<TEXT>
a roofer fell off a roof onto a live 
electrical line monday where he hung for 20 minutes until rescuers 
could shut off the power and lower him to safety 
jack robinson a subcontractor for roof pro of newberg near 
portland accidentally touched a 13000volt power line with a 
piece of sheet metal he was using to help roof a threestory 
apartment building 
the jolt knocked him from the roof and he landed on his abdomen 
on a 110volt wire about 30 feet above a sidewalk he was 
eventually removed by a fire crew using a cherry picker 
by the grace of god i didnt hit the sidewalk jack robinson 
said from his bed in emanuel hospital and health center where he 
was being treated for burns to his hands and his thigh 
the first few thoughts that went through my mind were my wife 
and kids and my life insurance policy because i figured this was 
it he said 
portland fire bureau crews arrived within minutes told robinson 
to hang on and placed mattresses gathered from apartments on the 
ground and held a safety net 
bureau spokesman neil heesacker said firefighters were 
reluctant to put a ladder up to get him because the minute they 
touched him they would ground him and probably electrocute him 
portland general electric shut off the power and dispatched a 
picker which firefighters used to rescue robinson 
robinsons boss max wright said robinson was working on a 
ledge on the top of the roof when an 8foot piece of sheet metal 
robinson was carrying touched the power line 
as he fell he landed on a wire down below it kind of caught 
him across the middle wright said his legs were hanging on 
one side and his torso was on the other 
wright said robinson managed to maintain a sense of humor about 
the incident even telling a coworker this is the way you dont 
do it as he hung from the wire 
