<TEXT>
here is a chronology of the life of stormie 
jones the worlds first heart liver transplant who died sunday at 
the age of 13 
feb 14 1984 her liver and heart damaged by a condition 
giving her abnormally high blood cholesterol stormie becomes the 
first person to receive a heartliver transplant she is 6 
oct 26 1988 she returns to childrens hospital of pittsburgh 
for removal of an obstruction to her bile ducts 
jan 8 1988 she is readmitted because of rising enzyme 
levels a sign of possible organ rejection 
nov 3 1989 she suffers an episode of liver rejection and 
begins receiving the experimental antirejection drug fk506 
jan 6 1990 she returns to pittsburgh with suspected 
hepatitis 
feb 20 1990 her liver damaged from hepatitis she receives a 
second transplanted liver she is discharged 17 days later 
may 20 1990 the dosage of fk506 is increased after stormie 
suffers a rejection episode 
june 23 1990 tests confirm a second case of hepatitis and 
doctors administer a proteinlike substance to bolster stormies 
immune system 
nov 11 1990 stormie returns a final time to childrens 
hospital with flulike symptoms she dies at 952 am after 
respiratory distress and a cardiac arrest 
