hundreds of angry farmers used tractors bales of 
hay and barricades of burning tires to block traffic monday on 
major highways near everal cities in central france 
one group of farmers intercepted a belgian truck carrying 
imported beef and seized all of the eightton cargo except a 
portion destined for charity organizations 
the protests were the latest in a sixmonth campaign by farmers 
who contend that the government is not protecting them against 
lowpriced meat imports and the effects of drought a decision last 
week by the european community to reduce state subsidies to farmers 
also has drawn criticism 
the blockades were mounted for four hours on several roads in 
the limousin poitoucharentes and auvergne regions of westcentral 
and central france an estimated 2000 farmers were involved 
