<TEXT>
a moderate earthquake rumbled 
through the northwestern yugoslav republic of slovenia but there 
was no apparent damage the tanjug news agency reported monday 
the quake registered 42 on the richter scale and is believed 
to have been centered near bohinjska bistrica in the northwest 
corner of the country near the italian and austrian borders 
it struck late sunday evening and was followed by a serious of 
minor tremors tanjug said 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude 
an earthquake of 4 on the richter scale can cause moderate 
damage 
