detention under rightwing governments has died his family said 
monday he was 81 
ritsos died at home late sunday a nephew said no cause of 
death was given but ritsos had suffered from various ailments 
recently 
several athens dailies reported that ritsos had become 
despondent with the collapse of communism in eastern europe over 
the past year and had shut himself off from society 
ritsos was one of greeces most prolific and popular poets his 
work ranging from long ideological pieces to personal lyricism 
gained a wide following when it was set to music by composers such 
as mikis theodorakis 
he was detained or sent into internal exile for many years under 
rightwing governments and the 196774 military dictatorship he 
refused to compromise his beliefs for the sake of his personal 
freedom 
harilaos florakis president of the greek communist party of 
which ritsos was a member said monday 
we are filled with great sorrow yannis ritsos identified 
himself with the best that modern greece had to offer 
ritsos won the soviet unions lenin peace prize in 1978 and 
numerous literary awards many from eastern bloc countries 
he was nominated for the nobel prize for literature several 
times 
