<TEXT>
thousands of celebrants filled the 
streets of this african country on monday for the crowning of the 
new king of lesotho 
formerly known as prince mohato the new king is the 27yearold 
son of exiled king moshoeshoe ii who was dethroned last week by 
the head of the countrys ruling military council maj gen justin 
lekhanya 
queen regent mamohato the new kings mother attended mondays 
ceremony held beneath a statue of king moshoeshoe i the new 
kings greatgreatgrandfather 
no royal name has been given the new king but he was expected 
to be called king letsie iii he will be the constitutional monarch 
and head of state but with no executive powers 
moshoeshoe was forced into exile in march following 
disagreements with lekhanya who seized power in a 1986 coup 
lekhanya gave the king some executive authority but in 
february he fired most of moshoeshoes supporters from the 
government and told the king to leave when he refused to approve 
replacements 
last month lekhanya invited moshoeshoe back from exile in 
london but he said last week the king had set unacceptable 
conditions for returning and therefore had been stripped of his 
title and powers 
lekhanya said one condition set by moshoeshoe was dissolution of 
the government 
it was not clear if moshoeshoe would return to lesotho 
lekhanya said the deposed king had been granted amnesty and a 
government news release monday said none of moshoeshoes property 
would be confiscated 
lesotho is a mountainous landlocked country of about 15 
million people completely surrounded by south africa lesotho 
gained independence from britain in 1966 
lekhanya has promised to return lesotho to civilian rule in 
1992 
