<TEXT>
the countdown toward this weeks 
launch of the space shuttle atlantis proceeded without mishap 
monday after months of delays caused by fuel leaks and lastminute 
problems with a spy satellite 
nasa plans to send up atlantis sometime between 630 pm and 
1030 pm est thursday its fifth nighttime shuttle launch 
because the defense department flight is secret the exact time 
will not be announced until nine minutes before liftoff 
nasa spokeswoman lisa malone said the countdown which began 
sunday night was proceeding smoothly we dont have any 
problems she said 
weather forecasts were less favorable air force meteorologists 
predicted a 40 percent chance of good weather at launch time 
as with the six previous pentagon missions the national 
aeronautics and space administration refused to discuss the 
shuttles cargo or provide any flight details the mission is 
expected to last about four days during which atlantis five 
astronauts are to deploy a satellite that reportedly will spy on 
iraq and other areas 
the mission originally was scheduled for july but was delayed 
indefinitely after atlantis sprang dangerous hydrogen leaks similar 
to those afflicting the shuttle columbia nasa temporarily grounded 
the entire fleet in june 
nasa tried three times in late august and september to launch 
columbia but it was forced to halt two countdowns because of 
leaking hydrogen and another because of problems with the 
astronomical observatory it was to carry 
