<TEXT>
from ministers son to congressman to prison 
inmate robert garcia has followed the advice in one of his 
favorite hymns in good times praise his name and in the bad 
times do the same 
and thats the message he wants to share as he embarks on a new 
career in prison ministry garcia said 
nothing guarantees a smooth easy life the 57yearold 
garcia said in a recent interview by knowing god we have the 
ability to handle it and thats all we can ask for in life 
five months after an appeals court reversed his conviction in 
the wedtech corp scandal garcia has joined prison fellowship 
ministries the organization founded by chuck colson of watergate 
notoriety 
in terms of their spiritual lives its important that inmates 
understand our relationships with god are the most important thing 
we have he said 
garcia says his faith has carried him through since january 197 
when several wedtech officers pleaded guilty to paying bribes to 
obtain military contracts and gave prosecutors names of those they 
said were involved 
the democratic congressman who represented the south bronx 
neighborhood where wedtech was located was among several local 
politicians charged in the corruption scheme garcia and his wife 
jane were accused of demanding payoffs from wedtech in return for 
his influence in washington 
a jury convicted them last year of extortion and both were 
sentenced to three years in prison with the recommendation they be 
released on parole after serving six months garcia resigned his 
congressional seat on jan 19 after his conviction 
he spent 104 days at the minimumsecurity federal prison at 
eglin air force base in florida before the conviction was 
overturned in june the appeals court which found the jury had not 
been properly instructed on the law left open the possibility of a 
new trial for garcia and his wife who remained free while their 
appeal was being heard 
federal prosecutors decided to continue the case and the garcias 
will be retried beginning next month unless a judge accepts their 
argument that they cant be tried twice for the same offense 
garcia has a wide range of experience with prison life 
as a young state senator from the bronx he was called on to 
serve as a negotiator during the bloody uprising at the attica 
state prison in 1971 
he also served as chairman of the state senates crime and 
correction committee which required his visiting many of the 
states facilities 
