results but it sure is worth the effort said abelardo coimbra 
bueno 26 who flew his hang glider over rios mountains to drop 
dozens of sacks of seeds into forest clearings 
five people in hang gliders soared over rios mountaintop tijuca 
forest and dumped nearly 1 million seeds into the worlds largest 
urban park which sprawls over famed corcovado mountain 
the dense forest almost completely destroyed a century ago 
before being replanted with native trees was recently named a 
national heritage park by president fernando collor de mello 
