<TEXT>
dutch authorities handed an air 
force sergeant over to us military authorities monday after they 
promised not to execute him for killing and dismembering his wife 
staff sgt charles d short 34 of highwood ill was 
delivered to the 32nd tactical air force squadron in soesterberg 
said justiceministry spokesman victor holtus that ended a 
twoyear battle over which country had the right to try short 
in 1988 a dutch court sentenced him to six years in jail for 
slaying his turkishborn wife dismembering her and dumping the 
remains in plastic bags 
the dutch high court ultimately overturned the sentence saying 
authorities here had no jurisdiction over the us serviceman 
but in a separate ruling in march the high court said short 
could not be surrendered to the united states as long as he could 
face the death penalty 
us military authorities issued a written guarantee that short 
would not be sentenced to death justice ministry officials said 
the dutch have no capital punishment and refuse to extradite 
anyone who could be executed elsewhere 
holtus said it wasnt known where short would ultimately stand 
trial 
</TEXT>
