leftist guerrillas killed five children 
and two policemen monday when they ambushed a police vehicle 
authorities said 
the revolutionary armed forces of colombia or farc ambushed 
the police vehicle on a bridge near the southern town of algeciras 
according to a police statement 
the rebels apparently thought the vehicle was carrying 
policemen instead it was being used to transport boys and girls 
who were receiving instruction under a youth auxilary police 
program four children also were wounded 
on saturday the farc joined another guerrilla group the 
national liberation army or eln in carrying out the biggest rebel 
offensive so far this year 
the army announced monday that the rebel death toll from the 
fighting in two northern colombian towns had risen to 26 after four 
more bodies of guerrillas were found in a common grave 
rebels retreating saturday from the towns of taraza and caceres 
were carrying several more dead and wounded with them according to 
official statements 
nine soldiers and a police officer also died in the battle 
which took place days after the two guerrilla groups offered to 
enter peace talks with the government of president cesar gaviria 
a government statement said the attack had convinced it that 
such talks were impossible until the rebels demonstrated their 
desire for peace through action 
the farc and the eln are the countrys oldest and most active 
guerrilla groups 
another rebel group the national peoples army has maintained 
a ceasefire while talking peace with the government leaders of 
the group have said it will disarm in december 
