<TEXT>
a new generation of indian writers has 
burst forth winning acclaim at home and abroad for everything from 
sonnets to satire 
inspired by salman rushdie and others they are irreverently 
testing the limits of language and venturing into styles rarely 
seen in their homeland 
while some critics say it smacks of elitism most write in 
