spending in 1989 says eric mcdowell a juneau consultant 
but tourism rebounded last summer except at some fishing 
lodges which still suffer from lingering concerns about tainted 
fish mcdowell says 
stan stephens a valdez tourboat operator says his business 
this summer was back to prespill levels while some people may be 
avoiding the sound stephens says about a third of his customers 
ask to see bligh reef the submerged rock that ripped open the 
exxon valdezs hull 
