his party the hong kong democratic foundation wants to 
insulate the territory from chinese influence it says more 
legislative seats should be elected by direct vote and laws should 
be passed to guarantee basic liberties 
in mcgregors view china understands only confrontation 
during the 1967 crisis mcgregor then an official in the 
department of commerce and industry violated protocol by closing 
the territorys procommunist schools he believed bombs were being 
made in chemistry labs 
what saved him from losing his job mcgregor said was a 
laboratory explosion that blew off a students arm 
the way to beat these men is to fight them tooth and nail 
he said 
kwok contends mcgregors pugnacious attitude could hurt the 
territory 
if you make the chinese lose face by forcing them into a 
corner they will never forget it he said we must 
cooperate 
according to kwok the territorys relationship to china is like 
a bridge game in which beijing holds the best hand 
weve got one trump card money he said they hold 
everything else if they get really mad they can turn off the 
water and the lights then where would we be 
kwok recalls growing up with stories about communist authorities 
promising his relatives they wouldnt touch the factories 
warehouses and department store in shanghai 
in the end an empire of nine textile mills one of the biggest 
department stores in shanghai and 20000 employees disappeared 
shrewd business deals in hong kong propelled the family back to 
prosperity and their wing on co is worth more than 100 million 
kwok was educated at harvard and mit where he received a doctorate 
in computer science 
the shanghai experience did not turn the family against china 
and kwok noted hong kong is different than shanghai its 
protected by an international agreement 
he and his party colleagues also have their own interests to 
protect many members are leading businessmen with substantial 
stakes in chinas development like the kwok familys company 
in early 1988 wing on completed renovating shanghais first 
great department store which opened in september 1918 the kwok 
family once owned it 
