she also showed a flair for songwriting an aunt lent her 7000 
to finance a nashville showcase performance which caught the 
attention of rca records she signed an rca recording contract in 
1986 at a time when most record companies were looking for singers 
almost half her age 
oslin became one of nashvilles most intriguing personalities 
launching a new career in her mid40s and writing songs from the 
