<TEXT>
doctors are trying to find out why some older 
patients in hospitals get well physically but never seem to recover 
emotionally 
the illness gets better but the patient gets worse said 
robert m palmer a geriatrician at university hospitals of 
cleveland 
palmer and dr c seth landefeld recently received a 485000 
grant from the john a hartford foundation to study elderly 
patients affected by dysfunctional syndrome 
the doctors said some patients who are hospitalized can no 
longer perform simple tasks such as walking bathing and dressing 
when there seems to be no physical reason 
landefeld said up to 30 percent of patients over 75 lose some 
ability 
part of the grant was used to remodel a hospital unit to 
determine whether a change in atmosphere can reduce the incidence 
of the syndrome the 15bed unit which opened in july represents 
a departure in the way such patients are cared for the doctors 
said 
greater emphasis is placed on how well a patient is eating 
walking sleeping and using the bathroom and on signs of 
depression 
the doctors plan to compare how well patients do in the new unit 
with results from other hospital units 
 
