<TEXT>
new tests for impaired balance in older people 
may help discover a way to anticipate and prevent falls one of the 
chief hazards to the overall health of the elderly researchers 
report 
the balance tests involve how far one can reach while standing 
researchers at duke university and at the veterans 
administration medical center at durham nc conclude that the 
test may be useful not only for measuring balance but for detecting 
change in balance over time and helping in the design of protective 
environments for balanceimpaired older people 
reporting in the november issue of the journal of gerontology 
pamela w duncan of dukes center for the study of aging says using 
the act of reaching as a measure is practical and can easily be 
performed at home or in nursing homes 
