<TEXT>
combining anemic puns with relevant 
statistics louis rukeyser grins and winks his way into the homes 
of 10 million television viewers every friday 
since 1970 rukeyser has demystified the jargon and gyrations of 
the economy his irreverant attitude toward the oftenstuffy 
subject has made his show wall street week one of the most 
popular half hours on public tv 
a 20th anniversary program with some of the shows best guests 
will air friday from the popular tavern on the green restaurant in 
new york a onehour retrospective will follow on next monday 
the rakish whitehaired rukeyser is one of the most durable 
television personalities on the air rivaling veteran luminaries 
such as mr rogers johnny carson and julia child 
he is known for painful fits of prose once while answering a 
viewers letter on investing in a hairpiece manufacturer rukeyser 
said if all your money seems to be hair today and gone tomorrow 
well try to make it grow by giving you the bald facts on how to 
get your investments toupee 
after a market slump he considered changing the name of the 
show to wall street wake he often consoles viewers by telling them 
to remember that its only their money not their life 
we have in america a bad tendency that things have to be 
either serious or fun he said before taping the show at 
maryland public television in suburban baltimore whereas in real 
life this isnt true the teachers we all remember in high school 
and college were not the ones who put us to sleep i dont think 
any of us should apologize for not being dull 
nobody wants to come home on a friday to be educated first 
you have to pull them into the tent 
along the way rukeyser was dubbed by people magazine as the 
only sex symbol of the dismal science of economics the new 
york daily news identified him as the economic guru of the 
industry 
outside of the wall street journal rukeyser has been a 
pioneer in demonstrating the popular appeal of quality business 
journalism said thomas rosenstiel a media cretic for the los 
angeles times he is especially good at proving that this stuff 
can be interesting and useful without being deadly dull 
rukeyser 57 appears each week with three panelists chosen 
from a pool of money managers and financial analysts who question 
the guest of the week such as the chairman of the securities and 
exchange commission or noted economist john kenneth galbraith 
in addition technical analysts whom he calls elves vote on a 
weekly elves index that assesses the strength or weakness of 
the economy 
rukeyser doesnt makes any predictions other than to say he is a 
longterm bull he constantly issues disclaimers on stock tips 
offered by guests of the show nonetheless their recommendations 
often cause share prices to rise sharply the week after the show 
airs 
ralph acampora head of prudentialbache securities technical 
analysis division and one of rukeysers elves credits him with 
starting business coverage on tv 
when i started with prudential i told them i wanted a big 
chart room and a television acampora said they asked me why i 
wanted a tv and i told them mrs obrien sitting at home has the 
greatest information in the world 
that mythical viewer is watching business news on cable news 
network and financial news network and its all because of lou 
acampora said 
rukeyser a former foreign correspondent for abc and the 
baltimore sun became the first economic commentator for a 
network in 1968 with abc he moonlighted on the pbs show for three 
years before leaving abc complaining about television coverage of 
economics 
he still maintains economics is the most poorly covered area of 
american journalism 
the prevailing view is that the subject of economics is too 
dull andor too complicated to hold an audience larger than the 
capacity of your average telephone booth he said i think 
thats nonsense i think there is a hunger in the american public 
for clear believable understandable usable pocketbook 
information 
despite his bullish outlook he concedes the economy is 
currently looking bleak but hes quick to remind anyone that he 
doesnt invest for shortterm profit 
punk anemic weak getting weaker the outlook for the next 
few months is soggy at best rukeyser said but even with 
minimal policy changes we can be on our way again by 1992 
rukeyser who also writes a syndicated newspaper column 
lectures and has written two books is known for being tough on his 
panelists and guests he continually pleads with them to speak in 
english 
jargon is a very convenient shield for people not entirely 
sure of what they are saying he said 
rukeyser says he will continue doing the show as long as it is 
fun which it still is and as long as his audience still wants 
him 
or as he might put it his stock may be maturing but his 
ratings are bullish and the dividends rewarding so rally round 
the tube in confidence the guru will keep your interest primed 
