disarray 
when it rains lines go dead on sunny days calls dialed 
correctly often ring the wrong number or get crossed so that 
several voices are heard fax and computer tramsmissions break off 
because of the weak quality of the lines 
as many as 500000 lines one of every seven may be out of 
