the talks launched in 1986 are meant to end by dec 7 with 
farreaching agreements to reduce barriers to trade in 15 sectors 
hopes of progress in agriculture the linchpin in the entire 
talks were dashed saturday when the united states and a group of 
farm exporting nations rejected a european community proposal on 
cuts in farm supports they also said offers from japan and south 
korea were inadequate 
the ec hasnt yet demonstrated to others that it has the 
flexibility to negotiate a package deputy us trade 
representative rufus yerxa said in a telephone interview 
