the 12nation trading bloc submitted its proposal only last 
thursday after a months internal wrangling it offers an overall 
30 percent cut in farm supports but does not give commitments in 
specific areas the cuts over 10 years would be backdated to 1986 
thus giving the ec credit for measures already taken 
an ec official who requested anonymity described the offer as 
substantial he urged washington to adopt a more realistic 
approach to cuts in farm support 
the united states and the 14nation cairns group of farm 
exporters have proposed reductions of 75 percent in internal 
supports and import barriers they want export subsidies to be 
slashed by 90 percent as these are considered the most trade 
distorting the reforms would take place over 10 years using 1991 
as baseyear 
japans offer also provides for a 30 percent cut in farm 
supports but makes no provision for reducing import barriers in 
particular tokyo has showed no sign of relaxing its ban on rice 
imports 
