<TEXT>
savings and loan regulator timothy ryan 
told thrift executives monday that his agency will make it easier 
for them to convert their institutions into commercial banks 
the move based on a legal opinion by office of thrift 
supervision chief counsel harris weinstein could hasten the end of 
sampls as a separate financial industry 
