the chairman of ab volvo monday promised an 
investigation of a phony television advertisement that portrayed a 
volvo withstanding the attempts of a monster truck to crush it 
volvo chairman pehr g gyllenhammar said in a statement that he 
would show customers suppliers and employees that i will never 
tolerate any kind of misconduct that will damage volvos name 
and excellent reputation 
the investigation would try to clarify how the ad came about and 
identify those resonsible he said 
volvo pulled the ads last week after admitting that the car in 
the ad had been reinforced the ads had been challenged by the 
texas attorney general 
volvo agreed to make no unproven claims run corrective 
newspaper ads and pay texas 316250 in investigative costs 
the ad filmed in austin appears to show a volvo as the only 
car left relatively intact after the truck runs over a line of 
autos 
it represents an insult to our company and what we represent 
and an insult against all volvo owners gyllenhammr said 
